WEBVTT

00:06.965 --> 00:08.675
[horses whinny]

00:10.468 --> 00:12.262
[animals chittering]

00:19.352 --> 00:20.270
[woman] Hi, there.

00:24.149 --> 00:25.024
You okay, hon?

00:32.449 --> 00:33.283
[sighs]

00:35.285 --> 00:36.327
What's your name?

00:38.496 --> 00:39.831
Garfield Logan.

00:41.207 --> 00:43.460
Garfield? Like the cat?

00:43.460 --> 00:45.670
I love that cat.

00:45.670 --> 00:48.798
My name's Kris.
I take care of the gorillas.

00:50.925 --> 00:52.552
[grunts]

00:55.972 --> 00:57.599
Do you like
gorillas, Garfield?

00:59.309 --> 01:02.020
Okay. You just sit here
and watch them a minute.

01:03.563 --> 01:05.315
[breathing heavily]
I don't wanna be alone.

01:06.941 --> 01:09.569
You're gonna have to be, okay?

01:09.569 --> 01:12.864
I need to go
make an announcement
so we can find your parents.

01:12.864 --> 01:14.699
I'm sure they're
as worried as you are.

01:17.535 --> 01:19.287
I'll be right back, sweetie.

01:24.959 --> 01:27.128
[crying]

01:32.550 --> 01:33.593
[gorilla grunts]

01:35.345 --> 01:36.513
[grunting]

01:40.892 --> 01:42.852
[foreboding music playing]

01:46.731 --> 01:48.983
[grunting]

01:53.279 --> 01:54.781
[monitor beeping]

01:56.074 --> 01:57.367
[monkey screeching]

01:58.368 --> 02:00.036
[gorilla growling]

02:00.662 --> 02:01.996
[sobbing]

02:03.081 --> 02:03.915
[growls]

02:07.377 --> 02:08.503
[growls]

02:08.503 --> 02:09.420
[grunts]

02:11.840 --> 02:14.300
[Dominic] <i>Garfield Logan.</i>

02:14.300 --> 02:16.261
[Rachel] <i>Gar, where are you?</i>

02:16.261 --> 02:17.720
Rachel!

02:17.720 --> 02:18.930
[Dick] <i>Gar!</i>

02:18.930 --> 02:19.889
Dick?

02:19.889 --> 02:23.143
[Dominic] <i>Yes.</i>

02:23.143 --> 02:25.144
<i>Protector of The Red.</i>

02:26.187 --> 02:27.021
[grunts]

02:29.232 --> 02:32.110
[Dominic] <i>I have found you.</i>

02:33.152 --> 02:34.028
[gasps]

02:37.907 --> 02:38.741
[groans]

03:03.683 --> 03:05.351
[fire crackling]

03:08.354 --> 03:09.355
[creature growls]

03:09.355 --> 03:11.357
Whoa! [grunts]

03:13.985 --> 03:15.570
[growling]

03:15.570 --> 03:19.449
[laughing] Welcome.

03:19.449 --> 03:21.075
- [Gar] Who are you?
- [laughs]

03:21.075 --> 03:22.827
[creature growls]

03:22.827 --> 03:23.786
What is that?

03:25.330 --> 03:28.833
Some loyal friends
working together.

03:28.833 --> 03:30.752
[Gar] "Friends?"

03:30.752 --> 03:32.253
Did he frighten you?

03:33.087 --> 03:34.964
A lion and a bat.

03:36.132 --> 03:37.133
[laughs]

03:38.259 --> 03:39.177
[chuckles nervously]

03:42.221 --> 03:44.432
[grunts]

03:50.188 --> 03:51.564
[growls]

03:54.525 --> 03:56.986
They are hungry,
so they go hunt.

03:58.363 --> 04:01.616
Ah, yes. And you?
Are you hungry?

04:04.994 --> 04:05.870
[Gar] Who are you?

04:08.331 --> 04:09.791
Where am I?

04:09.791 --> 04:12.085
[Dominic] You are atop
Mount Kilimanjaro.

04:14.712 --> 04:17.131
I pulled you here.
Out of The Red.

04:18.549 --> 04:19.801
The Red?

04:19.801 --> 04:22.929
The truth.
That is what
and who I am.

04:24.430 --> 04:25.598
Where are my friends?

04:25.598 --> 04:27.308
Who are you?

04:27.308 --> 04:29.143
[Dominic] I am
like you, my friend.

04:29.143 --> 04:33.314
I am one
with all beasts
who breathe and bleed.

04:35.525 --> 04:36.359
I...

04:38.695 --> 04:40.321
am your freedom.

04:46.828 --> 04:48.913
[theme music playing]

05:09.600 --> 05:10.768
[sighs]

05:10.768 --> 05:11.686
[grunts]

05:13.104 --> 05:17.108
The last thing I remember,
I was with my friends,

05:18.192 --> 05:19.861
facing the end, I guess...

05:21.654 --> 05:22.905
Then...

05:22.905 --> 05:24.699
[thrumming]

05:24.699 --> 05:25.867
Take me to The Red.

05:33.291 --> 05:34.167
What happened?

05:37.462 --> 05:39.213
You did what I told you to.

05:40.131 --> 05:41.632
You saved yourself.

05:47.305 --> 05:48.181
Then...

05:52.810 --> 05:54.187
I brought you here.

05:56.314 --> 05:57.523
Where are the Titans?

05:59.025 --> 06:00.026
I do not know.

06:02.111 --> 06:03.154
[mumbles]

06:05.448 --> 06:06.282
Come.

06:12.580 --> 06:15.708
Try some. Mmm.

06:15.708 --> 06:19.420
If you brought me here,
you can take me back.

06:19.420 --> 06:21.464
I'm a very good cook.

06:21.464 --> 06:22.924
I need to go home.

06:26.469 --> 06:27.762
[grunts]

06:27.762 --> 06:29.097
Take me to The Red!

06:31.015 --> 06:32.725
[breathing heavily]

06:32.725 --> 06:34.769
[shouts] Take me to The Red!

06:42.026 --> 06:42.860
[grunts]

06:45.154 --> 06:46.155
Why isn't it working?

06:46.155 --> 06:49.075
[sighs] You need your strength.

06:49.909 --> 06:51.077
You are famished.

06:52.370 --> 06:53.621
I can feel it.

06:55.873 --> 06:57.542
Now, sit.

06:57.542 --> 06:58.960
Eat what I offer you.

07:03.089 --> 07:04.132
Send me back.

07:05.675 --> 07:08.594
Only you can find your way
back through The Red.

07:10.388 --> 07:12.265
And what exactly is The Red?

07:15.226 --> 07:20.398
It is a force that connects
and pervades all animal life

07:20.398 --> 07:24.277
in this universe
and many others.

07:25.570 --> 07:27.029
A place fully alive,

07:27.029 --> 07:30.825
one that every
beating heart flows into.

07:30.825 --> 07:36.205
Only a chosen few
can tap into its raw power.

07:39.000 --> 07:42.378
The Green Plague
that killed your parents,

07:42.378 --> 07:44.088
also it changed you.

07:45.256 --> 07:48.342
That disease didn't change me.

07:49.510 --> 07:51.220
A lunatic called the Chief did.

07:52.430 --> 07:53.681
Dr. Niles Caulder...

07:54.849 --> 07:57.059
cured me of the Green Plague.

07:58.311 --> 07:59.896
I was its only survivor.

08:01.314 --> 08:02.273
I know.

08:04.942 --> 08:07.403
Sakutia killed my family, too.

08:09.280 --> 08:10.823
My sister and her children.

08:27.840 --> 08:28.716
I'm sorry.

08:30.635 --> 08:34.055
The outbreak took those
we love the most from us.

08:35.640 --> 08:37.308
That is why I brought you here.

08:38.267 --> 08:41.520
Our shared grief fuels us.

09:04.085 --> 09:05.419
I need your help.

09:13.261 --> 09:14.136
[Gar] Listen...

09:16.138 --> 09:18.557
We all have problems
these days, man, I--

09:18.557 --> 09:22.270
And I'm sure
yours are important.

09:22.270 --> 09:25.773
And if I can help you
in the future, I will.

09:27.525 --> 09:29.902
But right now,
I need to get
back to my friends.

09:33.364 --> 09:36.492
You have no idea
the evil we've been up against.

09:36.492 --> 09:40.246
Blood moons,
curses, demons. I...

09:42.873 --> 09:46.669
It may be
a matter of life and death
that I get back to my friends.

09:47.712 --> 09:50.965
Maybe for the entire world.

09:50.965 --> 09:54.760
You do not yet know
what truly threatens the world.

09:55.845 --> 09:57.305
[footsteps approaching]

09:59.098 --> 10:00.224
[explosion]

10:00.224 --> 10:01.517
- [security guard yelling]
- [gunshots]

10:02.310 --> 10:03.477
[grunts]

10:04.562 --> 10:06.230
[Dominic yells]

10:07.064 --> 10:08.566
[grunting]

10:08.566 --> 10:09.817
- [Gar growls]
- [Dominic] No.

10:09.817 --> 10:10.735
Stay.

10:10.735 --> 10:12.903
- [thuds]
- [gasps]

10:12.903 --> 10:15.031
- [security guard groans] No!
- [bone snaps]

10:19.577 --> 10:21.495
- [grunts]
- [security guard 2] Wait!

10:21.495 --> 10:23.289
- [thuds]
- [screams]

10:34.675 --> 10:36.135
[Dominic breathing heavily]

10:46.479 --> 10:47.772
Who were those guys?

10:47.772 --> 10:51.734
[Dominic] Men who
did not belong in my domain.

10:51.734 --> 10:54.070
They knew I sought to end them,

10:55.654 --> 10:57.448
so they struck first.

11:02.203 --> 11:05.539
When I wear
the helmet of The Beast,

11:08.167 --> 11:11.545
I can hear the apes
they took from the jungles...

11:12.880 --> 11:13.714
screaming.

11:13.714 --> 11:15.299
[apes screaming]

11:15.299 --> 11:16.717
[door creaking]

11:16.717 --> 11:19.136
[Dominic] <i>Rattling the bars
of their cages.</i>

11:20.012 --> 11:21.055
[door opens]

11:21.055 --> 11:22.723
<i>They are infected now.</i>

11:25.267 --> 11:26.727
<i>Dying.</i>

11:26.727 --> 11:27.895
[Dr. Myers] Keep her breathing.

11:29.605 --> 11:30.439
But Dr. Myers--

11:30.439 --> 11:33.484
I need the data. Scalpel.

11:33.484 --> 11:36.195
[Dominic] <i>Dissected while
still alive.</i>

11:37.154 --> 11:38.447
[ape growls]

11:38.447 --> 11:39.949
Put some tape over its mouth

11:39.949 --> 11:41.992
- to shut it up, for God's sake.
- [ape groans]

11:48.791 --> 11:50.584
I need to free the apes

11:50.584 --> 11:53.295
and burn their lab
to the ground.

11:56.006 --> 11:59.802
The disease that killed
my sister and her children,

12:01.595 --> 12:05.057
your parents,
and dozens of others,

12:06.267 --> 12:09.437
it came
from this same lab, Gar.

12:10.354 --> 12:11.939
What?

12:11.939 --> 12:15.901
It is finally
time for us to get
justice for our families.

12:17.653 --> 12:21.449
This is our sacred mission.

12:23.284 --> 12:25.286
You know so much about me.

12:26.704 --> 12:29.665
Are you gonna
tell me something about you?

12:32.501 --> 12:33.335
[grunts]

12:40.176 --> 12:43.721
I was once Dominic Mndawe.

12:45.055 --> 12:48.517
But the day Mike Maxwell
gave me this helmet,

12:48.517 --> 12:50.811
there was only Freedom Beast.

12:57.443 --> 12:59.904
Beyond tying me to The Red,

12:59.904 --> 13:01.489
this ancient helm

13:02.281 --> 13:04.825
prolonged my lifespan.

13:04.825 --> 13:07.161
It gave me strength, stamina,

13:07.161 --> 13:11.624
and the ability
to fuse two creatures
into one super-hybrid.

13:13.292 --> 13:14.585
Weirdest power ever.

13:18.839 --> 13:21.675
The legend of The Beast

13:21.675 --> 13:26.096
goes back
as far as the story
of Mkunare and Kanyanga.

13:26.096 --> 13:31.227
Each one of us
protected our time
as best we could

13:31.227 --> 13:33.187
with the tools we were given.

13:38.859 --> 13:40.945
But you need no helmet.

13:41.946 --> 13:44.198
You are different from us.

13:44.198 --> 13:46.575
From Animal Man, or Vixen,

13:46.575 --> 13:48.911
or the others tied to The Red.

13:50.162 --> 13:52.122
You can do more than them, Gar.

13:52.873 --> 13:53.832
Than me.

13:57.169 --> 14:00.172
I brought you here
to show you that.

14:00.172 --> 14:04.718
To free your mind
of the cage society puts it in.

14:09.056 --> 14:12.685
If I'm more
connected to The Red
than anybody else,

14:14.436 --> 14:17.356
why is it that I only turn
into green animals?

14:20.317 --> 14:25.239
Your favorite color
is green, no?

14:25.239 --> 14:28.742
Yeah, I mean, [chuckles]
it's been that way ever
since I was a kid.

14:28.742 --> 14:32.496
Your influence
over The Red is astounding.

14:36.959 --> 14:37.918
Drink this.

14:39.837 --> 14:43.424
[chuckles]
What does it do?
Make me grow or shrink?

14:45.843 --> 14:46.969
A bit of both.

14:48.137 --> 14:49.346
It destroys you.

14:50.848 --> 14:54.101
See your truth, stop this lab,

14:54.935 --> 14:56.437
and you will travel back

14:56.437 --> 15:00.065
through The Red
on your own in moments.

15:06.822 --> 15:07.656
Now.

15:12.578 --> 15:13.621
Let it begin.

15:14.204 --> 15:15.205
[swishes]

15:29.595 --> 15:31.555
[breathing deeply]

15:38.854 --> 15:39.855
[grunts]

15:42.274 --> 15:43.275
[groans]

15:47.946 --> 15:50.157
How long does it take to begin?

15:52.076 --> 15:54.787
[chuckling] How long
does it take to begin?

15:54.787 --> 15:56.622
How long is it
gonna take to begin?

15:56.622 --> 15:58.874
[shouting] How long
does it take to begin?

15:58.874 --> 16:01.418
[crying] How long
does it take to begin?

16:01.418 --> 16:02.670
How long does it take to begin?

16:02.670 --> 16:04.254
How long
is it gonna take to begin?

16:04.254 --> 16:06.256
[laughs]

16:06.256 --> 16:09.760
[Dominic] <i>Breathe.</i>

16:13.222 --> 16:14.598
[thrumming]

16:17.935 --> 16:18.811
[gasps]

16:19.770 --> 16:20.771
[panting]

16:27.194 --> 16:28.654
[clinking]

16:30.489 --> 16:32.324
[tense music playing]

16:35.119 --> 16:36.328
[Rachel] <i>Where are we going?</i>

16:38.038 --> 16:39.456
[thrumming]

16:40.374 --> 16:41.625
[gags]

16:48.382 --> 16:49.216
[gasping]

16:53.887 --> 16:54.763
[Rachel] Gar?

16:56.682 --> 16:57.725
Earth to Gar.

16:59.143 --> 17:00.018
Where are we going?

17:02.354 --> 17:03.439
I don't know.

17:03.439 --> 17:04.690
[Rachel] Yes, you do.

17:04.690 --> 17:06.567
You are in the
driver's seat this time.

17:08.277 --> 17:09.111
No.

17:10.320 --> 17:11.572
Where's Dick?

17:11.572 --> 17:12.614
[beeping]

17:14.324 --> 17:16.076
Now that we're all here,

17:16.076 --> 17:18.537
[chuckles] how about
some tunes?

17:19.705 --> 17:22.166
[music playing on radio]

17:22.166 --> 17:24.668
You've always
followed everybody else, Gar.

17:25.627 --> 17:27.087
I sure have.

17:27.087 --> 17:28.756
First, your parents,

17:28.756 --> 17:31.467
then Dr. Caulder, then Dick.

17:31.467 --> 17:33.093
Like a lost puppy.

17:33.093 --> 17:34.011
Shut up!

17:34.970 --> 17:36.597
It's time to stop following.

17:38.098 --> 17:42.478
♪ <i>There's a time
For us to let go ♪</i>

17:45.105 --> 17:50.611
♪ <i>There's a time
For holding on ♪</i>

17:50.611 --> 17:52.112
[thrumming]

17:52.112 --> 17:55.866
♪ <i>Time to speak
A time to listen ♪</i>

17:57.618 --> 17:59.536
[footsteps running]

18:02.164 --> 18:03.749
Don't worry about us, Gar.

18:06.210 --> 18:07.127
How can I not?

18:08.587 --> 18:09.505
You're my family.

18:11.048 --> 18:12.883
Return to your breath.

18:12.883 --> 18:15.010
[music continues]

18:17.221 --> 18:19.097
Go deeper.

18:24.895 --> 18:26.438
[thrumming]

18:28.065 --> 18:29.233
[gasps and grunts]

18:38.992 --> 18:40.869
[music fades]

18:41.537 --> 18:42.412
[Gar] Jinx.

18:43.080 --> 18:43.914
Hey.

18:49.545 --> 18:50.671
Am I dreaming?

18:50.671 --> 18:51.630
[Jinx] Ugh.

18:53.090 --> 18:56.093
Still asking
the boring questions, I see.

18:56.093 --> 18:57.678
Come on, Gar.

18:57.678 --> 19:00.305
Are you awake or asleep?

19:01.849 --> 19:02.808
Why not both?

19:05.936 --> 19:07.104
[softly] Am I dead?

19:07.104 --> 19:08.856
Mmm. No.

19:10.190 --> 19:12.484
But I am. Again.

19:13.443 --> 19:14.528
Thank you, Titans.

19:15.612 --> 19:17.698
I mean, mostly dead.

19:17.698 --> 19:19.616
This isn't my first funeral

19:20.826 --> 19:22.619
or eve of resurrection.

19:24.121 --> 19:27.124
It takes a while
to sort out who you are,

19:27.124 --> 19:29.209
but once you get
the hang of it,
it gets easier.

19:30.669 --> 19:32.754
It's a long story
someone else is writing.

19:36.800 --> 19:37.759
So, this is death?

19:39.553 --> 19:42.890
It's not exactly
what I expected
from death, initially.

19:44.224 --> 19:45.559
Kinda the same as life.

19:47.603 --> 19:51.773
Gar, it's really important
you understand this.

19:52.983 --> 19:56.028
Life isn't
about the individual.

19:56.028 --> 19:59.531
It's not a single pool
of water that evaporates.

19:59.531 --> 20:01.450
It's a collective.

20:01.450 --> 20:04.161
It's a river
that flows forever,

20:04.161 --> 20:07.873
our spirits mixing,
healthy or not, as a whole.

20:08.916 --> 20:09.833
As one.

20:12.044 --> 20:14.379
Forget yourself
and the Titans, Gar.

20:15.505 --> 20:18.091
This is all so much bigger.

20:18.091 --> 20:20.302
- [thrumming]
- [echoing]

20:24.389 --> 20:28.060
[Jinx] <i>Life flows
backwards and forwards.</i>

20:28.769 --> 20:29.853
[groans]

20:30.646 --> 20:31.688
All of us...

20:34.149 --> 20:35.817
go into The Red.

20:36.735 --> 20:39.655
Champions, guardians,

20:39.655 --> 20:41.990
protectors of all life,

20:41.990 --> 20:45.160
bound together
across the universe.

20:46.328 --> 20:48.580
Intersecting across space...

20:49.790 --> 20:50.666
and time.

20:53.210 --> 20:55.128
[thrumming]

20:55.921 --> 20:56.838
[groans]

21:04.054 --> 21:05.847
[Kris] You just sit here
and watch them a minute.

21:05.847 --> 21:09.142
[breathing heavily]
I don't wanna be alone.

21:09.142 --> 21:11.645
You're gonna have to be, okay?

21:11.645 --> 21:15.023
I need to go
make an announcement
so we can find your parents.

21:15.023 --> 21:17.484
I'm sure they're
as worried as you are.

21:17.484 --> 21:19.069
I'll be right back, sweetie.

21:24.074 --> 21:25.409
[crying]

21:37.170 --> 21:38.839
[thrumming]

21:43.927 --> 21:47.014
[Dominic] I know it is painful
to realize

21:47.014 --> 21:50.183
you are unlike anyone else
in this world.

21:56.940 --> 22:00.527
That you are absolutely alone.

22:02.029 --> 22:03.780
[young Gar groaning]

22:03.780 --> 22:06.908
But this is your path.

22:07.701 --> 22:09.119
[fire crackling]

22:13.206 --> 22:14.166
The heartbeats.

22:18.545 --> 22:19.963
Can you hear them?

22:19.963 --> 22:21.548
[hearts beating]

22:30.348 --> 22:31.266
Yes.

22:34.144 --> 22:36.229
Good.

22:44.946 --> 22:46.156
Then we can go.

22:50.702 --> 22:53.955
Come. Our mission awaits.

23:05.008 --> 23:07.928
[Dominic] The Red is under
attack, now more than ever.

23:09.721 --> 23:11.389
It needs its champions.

23:14.017 --> 23:16.895
You've been one a long time.

23:19.314 --> 23:20.398
Decades.

23:22.400 --> 23:24.694
Living alone in that cave
by yourself?

23:27.489 --> 23:29.574
When you become one
with The Red,

23:30.951 --> 23:33.745
individual relationships
lose their meaning.

23:35.413 --> 23:38.375
Like a bee with its hive.

23:42.712 --> 23:43.630
We are...

23:46.591 --> 23:47.759
above such things.

23:59.396 --> 24:01.314
[birds chirping]

24:22.836 --> 24:24.004
It looks closed.

24:25.213 --> 24:27.632
They do their worst work
at night.

24:31.303 --> 24:34.973
Can you hear them
screaming inside?

24:37.434 --> 24:39.728
[apes screaming]

24:46.234 --> 24:47.569
I can feel them, too.

24:50.447 --> 24:53.450
The men inside profit off pain.

24:55.493 --> 25:01.124
Predators no longer.
Tonight, they are prey.

25:08.381 --> 25:11.259
The helmet demands
their freedom.

25:18.141 --> 25:20.519
[alarm blaring]

